30/01/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia's Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva said Friday (28 January) that her country hopes to obtain official EU candidate status this year, as well as a date for starting accession talks. During a meeting with ambassadors of EU member states, Mitreva outlined the cabinet's plans for integration-related reforms. 
Meanwhile, Macedonian Deputy Prime Minister Radmila Sekerinska told the daily Utrinski Vesnik that Skopje has a realistic chance of achieving its EU-related goals, provided it conducts successful local elections, implements the decentralisation process on schedule, and launches judicial reform. (Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik, A1 TV - 29/01/05) 
